{
  "doc_id": "7380",
  "text": "In a previous study, we generated a panel of F1-hybrid mouse TSC lines that were used to measure molecular properties of the inactive X-chromosome [CITATION_1] . These TSCs were derived from reciprocal crosses between two diverse, inbred mouse strains, CAST/ EiJ (Cast) and C57BL/6J (B6). Using a high confidence, validated set of~18 million informative SNPs from [CITATION_2] , allelespecific gene expression can be measured accurately in these cells by the counting of SNPs contained within uniquely mapping highthroughput sequencing reads [CITATION_3] .",
